                            <comment id="17521421" author="dcapwell" created="Wed, 13 Apr 2022 02:53:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;marking 4.1 as this feature detects subtle bugs, so with this broken we could have subtle things failing, so we may actually have failing tests but think passing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17521489" author="benedict" created="Wed, 13 Apr 2022 06:29:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; avoided using AbstractCluster.uncaughtException&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It simply doesn&apos;t use &lt;tt&gt;Thread.getDefaultUncaughtExceptionHandler&lt;/tt&gt;, which appears to be how in-jvm dtests currently specify the uncaught exception handler that they monitor. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17522440" author="benedict" created="Thu, 14 Apr 2022 17:17:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This was more annoying than I would have liked, and the upgrade test I have introduced doesn&apos;t fully test the behaviour on 4.0 and back. We can strengthen that by implementing the &lt;tt&gt;executorFor&lt;/tt&gt; method on earlier versions of Cassandra if we like.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
